title.narrative: PARTNERSHIP FOR SOCIAL CHANGE FOR CHILDREN

description.narrative: Government and other partners, including children and adolescents, are engaged, mobilized and join efforts to drive social change for girls and boys, especially for Roma children and children with disabilities., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: National policies affecting children and adolescents and their families (especially those from Roma communities and those with disabilities) are evidence-based, equitable and adequately financed.

description.narrative: Child participation is high on the European Union's agenda thanks to the adoption of the Bucharest EU Children's Declaration, facilitated by UNICEF, the Romanian Children's Board and the Romanian Government during Romania's presidency of the EU Council. Furthermore, child rights remained at the top of the country's agenda in 2019 as a result of renewed partnerships with the Romanian Government, Presidency, Parliament, corporate sector, NGOs, media, influencers and children. Adolescents shared their opinions and valuable insights with top European decision- makers. Over three per cent of national child-related news was generated as a result of UNICEF events and initiatives. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
